The paper proposes a new deep learning approach to Kalman filtering for time-series data, which involves using a high-dimensional factorized latent state representation and locally linear dynamic models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SY).
